general_info: In 1960 Harris & Schroeder Builders, Inc. was formed as a partnership between H. Roland Harris & Glenn Schroeder.  Harris & Schroeder Builders, Inc. was incorporated on January 28, 1980.  Glenn Schroeder retired in 1992 and H. Roland Harris retired in 1997.  James M. Harris, a third generation builder has worked with his father most of his life and had been an equal partner since 1987 and a sole owner since 1998.  James M. Harris has been a Qualifier and State Licensed Building Contractor for Harris & Schroeder Builders since 1980.  For more that 50 years, Harris & Schroeder Builders, Inc. has helped owners navigate the issues and enjoy the process of building.  We not only deliver superior construction quality, but we put our clients first with ideas to save money, time and hassle.

general_info: Turk Construction Inc. is a residential and commercial general contractor. Located in Key Largo, Fla., the company has worked for a number of projects throughout South Florida ranging from small remodels of bathrooms, kitchens, interiors and exteriors to single family and multifamily homes. It has completed several commercial projects including storefronts, store interiors, commercial additions and renovations as well as all types of commercial new construction. Turk Construction Inc. offers a number of services, including planning, building foot print layout, value engineering, design consultation, preconstruction consultation, construction and project management and design-build services.

general_info: ABOUT OCEAN REEF... Ocean Reef is an exclusive, private community just 20 miles from the mainland at the tip of Key Largo, the largest of the picturesque Florida Keys. A ccessible by land, sea or air, the resort's 4, 000 acres are set apart in a private, protected world of unspoiled natural beauty. The club and resort offer social amenities, world class golf courses, tennis, boating, fishing and diving on North America's only living coral barrier reef. The community provides the safest, most secure setting for vacation activities and relaxation. Ocean Reef Club was originally purchased as a small fishing camp in 1945 by Minnea polis developer Morris Baker. A few years later, a small 26-room inn was built. The following years saw more progress as the boat channel and marina and first nine holes of golf were added. As the Club continued to grow, 26 villas were built in 1956 and more added each year thereafter. By this time, Ocean Reef Club had become world-renowned. In the spring of 1993, ownership of Ocean Reef Club passed to the property owner members who now operate the Club through its Board of Directors. Since the beginning, the Club's traditions and sense of community have been carefully maintained ; upholding a retreat-like atmosphere within family-friendly surroundings.
